<F P=106> [Unattributed article from Brussels EUROPE: "Solar Energy </F>
Policy Criticised"] 
  [Text] The Foundation for the Natural Heritage in Europe 
(Euronatur) has criticized research conducted in Germany and the 
European Union in promoting solar energy "which risks losing 
Europe one of the most important markets for the future." 
Contrary to the Japanese, which has set up large support 
programmes for developing solar energy, "Western Europe is 
continuing to waste billions" by betting on nuclear energy, 
thereby running the risk of leaving this large market to the 
Japanese, says no Euronatur. Another harmful consequence of 
this policy is that Eastern European countries should thus miss 
a "unique opportunity "of succeeding in their change in energy 
policy. Euronatur mentions as a concrete example the EU project 
to support the construction of two nuclear power plants in 
Ukraine and adds: "It is a scandal that public funds continue 
to be spent in the wrong directions." Euronatur deplores the 
fact that the promotion of solar energy is not mentioned in EU 
assistance programmes for Eastern Europe, which shows "that 
assistance programmes seem to have been conceived in cooperation 
with the nuclear lobby." 

</TEXT>

